## Shared Database Schema

### Core Shared Tables (used by ALL apps)

```sql
-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
-- CUSTOMERS — Single source of truth
-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
CREATE TABLE customers (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    auth_id     UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
    email       TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    phone       TEXT,
    first_name  TEXT,
    last_name   TEXT,
    company     TEXT,
    source      TEXT,  -- 'website', 'phone', 'referral', 'walk-in'
    notes       TEXT,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
-- VEHICLES — Linked to customers
-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
CREATE TABLE vehicles (
    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    customer_id UUID REFERENCES customers(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    year        INT,
    make        TEXT,
    model       TEXT,
    color       TEXT,
    vin         TEXT,
    license     TEXT,
    notes       TEXT,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);
```

### Payload CMS Tables (in `cms` schema — DO NOT EDIT DIRECTLY)

Payload auto-generates these tables in the **`cms`** Postgres schema via push mode:
- `cms.posts`, `cms.posts_tags`, `cms._posts_v` (blog posts + versions)
- `cms.categories` (blog categories)
- `cms.media` (uploaded files)
- `cms.projects`, `cms.projects_images` (portfolio/gallery)
- `cms.faqs` (FAQ items per page)
- `cms.testimonials` (client reviews)
- `cms.users`, `cms.users_sessions` (CMS admin users — separate from Supabase Auth)
- `cms.payload_preferences`, `cms.payload_preferences_rels`, `cms.payload_migrations` (internal)
- `cms.payload_locked_documents`, `cms.payload_locked_documents_rels`, `cms.payload_kv` (internal)
- `cms.services` (service definitions with pricing tiers, process steps, brands)
- `cms.promotions` (seasonal deals, discount codes, promotional banners)
- `cms.team_members` (staff profiles, certifications, specialties)
- `cms.site_settings`, `cms.homepage`, `cms.navigation` (globals — site-wide settings)

### Ticket System Tables (in `public` schema) ✅ CREATED

> Migration: `emwraps-tickets/supabase/migrations/001_create_all_tables.sql`
> Includes: auto-profile trigger, RLS policies, indexes, service catalog seed

| Table | Columns | Purpose |
|-------|---------|--------|
| `profiles` | id→auth.users, first_name, last_name, email, phone, position, role, specialties[], hourly_rate, status, avatar_url | Staff profiles |
| `customers` | id, auth_id, name, email, phone, first_name, last_name, company, customer_type, source, status, notes | Customer records |
| `vehicles` | id, customer_id→customers, year, make, model, trim, color, vin, license_plate, notes | Customer vehicles |
| `tickets` | id, ticket_id, customer_id→customers, vehicle_id→vehicles, customer_name, email, phone, car_*, services JSONB, service_day, end_date, notes, status, total_price | Core ticket data |
| `ticket_workers` | id, ticket_id→tickets, worker_id→profiles, role, notes, assigned_at, assigned_by | Worker assignments |
| `ticket_materials` | id, ticket_id→tickets, serial_number_id→serial_numbers, quantity_used, applied_area, warranty JSONB | Materials used |
| `bookings` | id, name, email, phone, service, preferred_date, vehicle_year/make/model, message, sms_consent, status | Frontend bookings |
| `products` | id, brand, model_sku, item_type, finish, color, description, cost_per_unit | Product catalog |
| `serial_numbers` | id, product_id→products, serial_number, item_type, brand, model_sku, color, width, length_remaining, quantity, status, location, notes | Inventory tracking |
| `service_structure` | id, name, structure JSONB | Service tree (seeded) |

**Auth Trigger**: `on_auth_user_created` → auto-creates `profiles` row for new auth users
**RLS**: All tables have RLS enabled. Authenticated users get full access. `bookings` and `service_structure` are public read.

