### Pages

| Page | Route | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| Dashboard | `/` | Stats overview, today's tickets, activity feed |
| Ticket List | `/tickets` | Filterable list with card/table views |
| Ticket Create | `/tickets/new` | Multi-step form with service tree selector |
| Ticket Detail | `/tickets/:id` | Full ticket view with services, materials, workers, print |
| Customer List | `/customers` | Searchable customer directory |
| Customer Detail | `/customers/:id` | Profile with vehicles & ticket history |
| Inventory | `/inventory` | Products, serial numbers, stock levels |
| Workers | `/workers` | Team overview with status selectors |
| Schedule | `/schedule` | Calendar view with day detail sidebar |
| Settings | `/settings` | Account info, service catalog (read-only), about |
| Login | `/login` | Email/password auth |

### Auth Model ✅ IMPLEMENTED

- **Roles**: `admin`, `manager`, `worker`, `staff`, `front_desk`

| Role | Access Level |
|------|-------------|
| **Admin** | Full access to all features, including user management |
| **Manager** | All except user management (`users.manage`) |
| **Front Desk** | Create tickets/customers, view all, process payments |
| **Worker** | View own assigned tickets, update status, upload photos |
| **Staff** | View-only access to tickets, customers, workers |

**Permission Matrix**: `src/lib/permissions.js` — 21 permission keys across 8 domains (tickets, customers, vehicles, inspections, inventory, workers, payments, settings)

**Enforcement Layers**:
- **Route-level**: `RoleGuard` component wraps each route in `App.jsx` — redirects to dashboard if unauthorized
- **UI-level**: `PermissionGate` component hides buttons/actions (e.g. Edit, Delete) from unauthorized roles
- **Sidebar**: Nav items filtered by permission — workers only see Dashboard + Tickets
- **Header**: Role label displayed next to user name with `ROLE_LABELS` mapping

### Key Design Decisions
- **UI/UX matches emwraps-react**: Same dark sci-fi HUD design system (amber/gold accent, Outfit font, glassmorphism)
- **Sidebar layout**: Collapsible sidebar for admin navigation
- **Service data**: CMS first → Supabase `service_structure` fallback → hardcoded fallback
- **CMS integration**: `src/lib/cms.js` fetches services from Payload CMS REST API
- **Same Supabase backend**: Shared auth/tables/RLS with frontend
- **Component size rule**: No single file exceeds 300 lines

### Key Files
- `src/lib/supabase.js` — Supabase client (shared project)
- `src/lib/cms.js` — CMS API client (services from Payload)
- `src/lib/permissions.js` — RBAC permission matrix (5 roles, 21 permissions)
